	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001091_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="left"><hi rend="underline">Private</hi></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Manchester</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">9<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> Sep<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">t</hi></hi></p>
<lb/><p>1857 </p>
<lb/><p>My dear <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Shaw</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I telegraphed 
<lb/>to <persName>Arrowsmith</persName>
<lb/>yesterday afternoon 
<lb/>and was truly 
<lb/>thankful to have 
<lb/>the map here in 
<lb/>time for a meeting

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001091_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/>of the chamber of 
<lb/>commerce this 
<lb/>morning at 11 AM. 
<lb/><choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>he Merchants came 
<lb/>out strongly about 
<lb/>a steamer for the 
<lb/><placeName>Zambesi,</placeName> and they 
<lb/>are to have a deputation 
<lb/>on the matter. </p>
<lb/><p>I put down 
<lb/>"com. member" on the 
<lb/>title page of the 
<lb/>book on the strength 
<lb/>of a belief that you 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001091_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'--> 
<lb/>will make me afterwards! 
<lb/>I shall write to <persName>Sir 
<lb/>Roderick</persName>, I suppose 
<lb/>via <persName>Lady M.</persName></p>
<lb/><p>Many thanks for 
<lb/>the map. I shall 
<lb/>take the liberty of 
<lb/>using it for 
<lb/><placeName>Scotland.</placeName> I left 
<lb/>the analysis of 
<lb/>Sichuana the 
<lb/>language of the 
<lb/><term type="tribe">Bechuanas</term> for <persName>Norris</persName> at <persName>Murray<reg>'</reg>s</persName>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001091_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'--> 
<lb/>some time ago. Has 
<lb/>he not got it<reg>?</reg>
<lb/>I should like to 
<lb/>know what he 
<lb/>thinks of it. Will 
<lb/>you be seeing him 
<lb/>say so &amp; he may 
<lb/>send or call for 
<lb/>it. <persName>Agnes</persName> is gone 
<lb/>to the <placeName>sea coast</placeName> with <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi>  L's sister 
<w>Vavass-<lb break="no"/>eur</w></persName> on account of her eyes. With kind 
<lb/>regards I am &amp;c </p>
<lb/><p><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
			
